data.description:

data.title: Acciona FY25 Profit Surges On Revenue Growth
data.description:
MADRID (dpa-AFX) - Acciona, S.A. (ACXIF, ANA.MC), a Spanish infrastructure and renewable energy firm, reported significantly higher profit in fiscal 2025, driven by growth in all segments.

In fiscal 2025, attributable net profit surged 90.4 percent to 803 million euros from last year's 422 million euros.

EBT climbed 82% year-over-year to 1.39 billion euros, and EBITDA grew 30.8 percent to 3.21 billion euros.

In the year, revenues were 20.24 billion euros, up 5.5 percent from 19.19 billion euros last year.

The company reported solid results in all business areas, driven by good performance and profitability of the Infrastructure business, successful execution of ACCIONA Energía's asset rotation plan, and Nordex's strong operating performance.

Further, ACCIONA's Board of Directors has proposed the distribution of a dividend of 310 million euros or 5.6 euros per share based on fiscal 2025 results.

data.title: UBS nominates Agustin Carstens and Luca Maestri as new board members
data.description:
UBS has nominated Agustin Carstens and Luca Maestri for election to the board of directors at its annual general meeting in April, the Swiss banking giant said on Friday.

They are to replace William C. Dudley and Jeanette Wong, who will not stand for re-election, UBS added.

"The addition of these two highly experienced leaders will further strengthen the board's expertise, bringing outstanding regulatory knowledge and extensive CFO skills," UBS Chairman Colm Kelleher said.
